It’s been a bit of a shitty week, well actually it’s not, it’s been a great work week, the dogs are fine, Simon is fine, life is pretty damn good...and yet my mood took a nose dive around Tuesday last week. I find nothing more frustrating and mentally draining than fighting against a mood which I don’t want to be in. I am pretty good at recognising my triggers and this helps me identify a reason as to why I’m low, but when I know I’ve stayed well clear of those triggers, well, this is just the worst. It’s a low for no good reason at all.
This past week there’s been a lot of smiling on the outside but not much smiling on the inside and I’m determined to not let it ruin another week of my life. Today I’m off to Thorpe Park 🎢 with @bangonstyle for a girly “I’m gonna shit my pants!” kinda day and I’m hoping all those thrill rides will shake this mood out of me. I’m afraid there’s no weekly vlog on YT today, blame the mood 😒, but I am vlogging this week so there should be one up next Tuesday and there will be plenty of Stories action too 😬
Another reminder of what you see on the gram ain’t always the reality ✌🏼

I was sent the most amazing and generous gift bag from Sky and if you saw my Stories from that day, you’ll have seen those beautiful Celine sunglasses that were inside. As you all know I love my Cèline ‘Baby Audrey’ sunglasses so much and because the ones in the gift bag are almost identical I thought it would be great to give them away to one of you guys ❤️ I want these beautiful sunglasses to go to someone who supports us, not just to some giveaway hunter who is only here for the freeby. So in spirit of that you do NOT have to make sure you’re following me and a million other accounts to enter, you don’t have to tag a mate or share the giveaway on your own feed. But what I would like you to do is comment below with your favourite episode of Friends. It’s not even relevant to the sunglasses but I figure everyone loves Friends and I’m pretty sure this will make us all have a giggle. I will pick a winner at random on Sunday evening and if you’re just a giveaway hunter then I’ll pick again 🙅🏼‍♀️

A gentle reminder for the start of the week, don’t be too hard on yourself and don’t force yourself to live up to the expectations of ‘The Gram’, it’s all just a showreel at the end of the day. I fall into this trap all too often and it’s a tough one to get out of at times. 
I read a tweet the other day that said it’s healthy to unfollow people who aren’t making you feel good. I often worry about the repercussions of unfollowing people because of the industry I work in, I don’t like drama, but I do like the mute button 🙊😉 You shouldn’t feel guilty if you unfollow someone. If their feed/their content is making you feel inadequate, jealous, sad or encouraging a behaviour you’re not happy with then it’s the right thing to do for you ♥️. This goes for me too, if my content evokes any of those negative feelings then go ahead and mute or unfollow my ass 🔇🙅🏼‍♀️

Long time no see eh guys? What have I missed?
You might have guessed that I did indeed take a little break from my social media platforms. If I’m being honest it wasn’t planned, hence why you had no notice but I can tell you it was very much needed. I love my job but sometimes there are things which are just more important to focus on, and I’m only human at the end of the day. 
Thank you all for sticking around and for all the lovely messages. I’m sorry I couldn’t reply to them but I literally didn’t open up my apps or log in to my accounts, it was a full on break from social media.

Anywho I’m back now, ready to share all my Spring outfits for the new season and YT videos will resume next week so stay tuned ❤️
(No Japan videos I’m afraid as I didn’t film)
